			"emoji": "üêù",
			"intro": "Every person alive today is here thanks to pollinators ‚Äì bees, wasps, butterflies, beetles and more. They are vital to all life on our planet but their habitats aren‚Äôt always protected. Anton investigates the pollinators found in Guernsey and the Pollinator Project ‚Äì a local initiative to help protect and raise awareness of their importance. I then tell of a traumatic event that happened to me several nights ago and the effect it had on my brain and body!",
			"links": [],
			"theme": "",
			"title": "You shouldn‚Äôt fear bees",
			"number": "16",
			"trailer": "",
			"features": [
				{
					"_uid": "2fa3132b-1928-43ca-8a2d-6a0aaa0546f5",
					"body": [
						{
							"_uid": "6fc31e5d-65b2-4c16-b5e4-1bd4621c9d50",
							"text": {
								"type": "doc",
								"content": [
									{
										"type": "paragraph",
										"content": [
											{
												"text": "Anton investigates the Pollinator Project an initiative created to help raise awareness of the importance of local pollinating wildlife.",
												"type": "text"
											}
										]
									}
								]
							},
							"component": "intro",
							"_editable": "\u003c!--#storyblok#{\"name\": \"intro\", \"space\": \"87028\", \"uid\": \"6fc31e5d-65b2-4c16-b5e4-1bd4621c9d50\", \"id\": \"14005712\"}--\u003e"
						},
						{
							"_uid": "8e0364dc-bd59-4a8d-83bb-16a433d8afc7",
							"text": {
								"type": "doc",
								"content": [
									{
										"type": "paragraph",
										"content": [
											{
												"text": "Set up in 2017 by La Soci√©t√© Guernesiaise their aims include:",
												"type": "text"
											}
										]
									},
									{
										"type": "bullet_list",
										"content": [
											{
												"type": "list_item",
												"content": [
													{
														"type": "paragraph",
														"content": [
															{
																"text": "increase the understanding of the important role pollinators play",
																"type": "text"
															}
														]
													}
												]
											},
											{
												"type": "list_item",
												"content": [
													{
														"type": "paragraph",
														"content": [
															{
																"text": "encouraging islanders to provide food and habitats for pollinators where possible, such as in gardens, allotments and window boxes",
																"type": "text"
															}
														]
													}
												]
											},
											{
												"type": "list_item",
												"content": [
													{
														"type": "paragraph",
														"content": [
															{
																"text": "work with schools, businesses and community groups to establish pollinator patches throughout the Channel Islands",
																"type": "text"
															}
														]
													}
												]
											},
											{
												"type": "list_item",
												"content": [
													{
														"type": "paragraph",
														"content": [
															{
																"text": "persuade large-scale land owners such as local government and utility companies to plant flowers, shrubs and trees for pollinators",
																"type": "text"
															}
														]
													}
												]
											},
											{
												"type": "list_item",
												"content": [
													{
														"type": "paragraph",
														"content": [
															{
																"text": "Discourage the use of pesticides and other harmful practices",
																"type": "text"
															}
														]
													}
												]
											}
										]
									},
									{
										"type": "paragraph",
										"content": [
											{
												"text": "This year they offered the perfect lockdown respite - find all 19 local butterflies. With restrictions in place due to Coronavirus they sent island households a mailer that encouraged families to explore closer to home and whilst out walking.",
												"type": "text"
											}
										]
									}
								]
							},
							"component": "text",
