					"title": "Anton Investigates: Pollinators",
					"component": "feature",
					"_editable": "\u003c!--#storyblok#{\"name\": \"feature\", \"space\": \"87028\", \"uid\": \"2fa3132b-1928-43ca-8a2d-6a0aaa0546f5\", \"id\": \"14005712\"}--\u003e"
				},
				{
					"_uid": "076295e8-3c07-4e63-a22f-3134ce2ef8bb",
					"body": [
						{
							"_uid": "a33ed813-534b-4718-99c3-6eb28cf385f4",
							"text": {
								"type": "doc",
								"content": [
									{
										"type": "paragraph",
										"content": [
											{
												"text": "A couple of days ago as I was getting ready for bed I passed Anton‚Äôs bedroom door I whispered a little good night to him as I always do. I then walked into my bedroom and my heart jumped out of my chest as something was hidden under my bed covers‚Ä¶",
												"type": "text"
											}
										]
									}
								]
							},
							"component": "intro",
							"_editable": "\u003c!--#storyblok#{\"name\": \"intro\", \"space\": \"87028\", \"uid\": \"a33ed813-534b-4718-99c3-6eb28cf385f4\", \"id\": \"14005712\"}--\u003e"
						},
						{
							"_uid": "964a04ff-3a75-49f9-a055-860ba52c6b53",
							"text": [
								{
									"_uid": "001fcba7-e56e-4430-90c4-3d562c8e0c74",
									"text": {
										"_uid": "58a6749d-41b6-4a40-b1a9-f524cec019fe",
										"type": "doc",
										"content": [
											{
												"_uid": "581b6908-39bf-42ce-9456-5653dffd3b16",
												"type": "paragraph",
												"content": [
													{
														"_uid": "8ca81d57-e03a-4011-a6e8-4c8773499897",
														"text": "This got me thinking, what is fear? How does it work? What actually happened in my chest? And more to the point, what was in my bed?",
														"type": "text"
													}
												]
											},
											{
												"_uid": "52206b2a-cb32-42b8-bbff-b2482cbd32ba",
												"type": "paragraph",
												"content": [
													{
														"_uid": "12ab6239-b199-4720-a4a1-d882cf6f1283",
														"text": "The feeling only lasted a fleeting moment, an involuntary response coming from deep within my brain. An ancient part of my being stemming from a time when were more lizard than human. I take Anton through the startle reflex - how our amygdala modulates and directs the signals in our brain, the role glutamate plays in a taking it deeper into more base reactions, the increase in adrenaline and the heart pumping harder ready for fight or flight.",
														"type": "text"
													}
												]
											}
										]
									},
									"component": "text",
									"_editable": "\u003c!--#storyblok#{\"name\": \"text\", \"space\": \"87028\", \"uid\": \"001fcba7-e56e-4430-90c4-3d562c8e0c74\", \"id\": \"14005712\"}--\u003e"
								}
							],
							"image": {
								"id": 1222947,
								"alt": null,
								"name": "",
								"focus": null,
								"title": null,
								"filename": "https://a.storyblok.com/f/87028/1600x1576/71dab76e70/amgydala.jpg",
								"copyright": null,
								"fieldtype": "asset"
							},
							"component": "image-and-text",
							"_editable": "\u003c!--#storyblok#{\"name\": \"image-and-text\", \"space\": \"87028\", \"uid\": \"964a04ff-3a75-49f9-a055-860ba52c6b53\", \"id\": \"14005712\"}--\u003e"
						},
						{
							"_uid": "427be877-5bed-40e8-a447-f77287e46c20",
							"quote": "If I put you in a situation where you feel unpleasant, anxious or nervous, you might have a heightened startle reflex. Whereas if I put you in a state where you are feeling pleasant and I am showing you materials you like and find pleasant, the startle reflex is usually reduced.",
							"quotee": "Professor Ottmar Lipp, Curtin University",
							"component": "quote",
							"_editable": "\u003c!--#storyblok#{\"name\": \"quote\", \"space\": \"87028\", \"uid\": \"427be877-5bed-40e8-a447-f77287e46c20\", \"id\": \"14005712\"}--\u003e"
